=======================================================================
PART 2 — Commercial License
=======================================================================

"Commercial Use" includes, but is not limited to:

  (a) Offering TeachAny or any derivative work as a paid product or
      service (e.g. SaaS, paid App, paid course platform).
  (b) Bundling TeachAny into enterprise training products sold to
      companies or institutions.
  (c) Using TeachAny within the course-delivery workflow of a
      for-profit education business.
  (d) Any use where revenue, subscription, per-seat fees, or similar
      monetization is attached to TeachAny's functionality.

"Non-Commercial Use" means:
  (a) Personal study, individual teaching preparation.
  (b) Public schools, universities, and non-profit education orgs
      using TeachAny internally at no charge to students.
  (c) Academic papers and open-source derivative projects released
      under AGPL-3.0.

If your intended use falls under "Commercial Use", you must obtain a
commercial license BEFORE deployment. Commercial licensing terms are
negotiable based on scale, user count, and integration scope.

Contact:
  GitHub Issues: https://github.com/weponusa/teachany/issues
                 (prefix your title with [Commercial])
  Email:         weponusa@gmail.com
  Details:       See COMMERCIAL-LICENSE.md in repository root.


